// make test-intllm-kernel-path (to be added):
//   Boot FajarOS with a .fjm v9 test model (small, bit-exact to Phase D's
//   Python simulator), then:
//     - ask "hello" (triggers tfm_mf_forward)
//     - Check: no saturation, no collapse, 5 argmax matches simulator
//
// Gate invariants:
//   1. mdl_v9_detect_format returns MDL_FORMAT_PHASE_D on test .fjm
//   2. tfm_mf_forward returns non-error (>=0) for all prompt tokens
//   3. No EXC: / PANIC: markers during forward
//   4. Generated tokens match Python simulator bit-exact (proves
//      kernel parity vs reference impl, §6.9 R3 baseline parity)
//
// Skeleton gate to add in Makefile:
//   test-intllm-kernel-path: iso-llvm test-models/intllm-tiny.fjm
//       @$(QEMU) ... boot ... ask hello ... > log
//       @grep "tfm_mf_forward returned" log && ...
